The paper discusses a numerical method for solving the nonlinear Schrödinger equation using finite-difference schemes, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The focus is on the Laplacian operator and its implementation, which suggests a sub-category of computational engineering (cs.CE). The paper also discusses computation and storage requirements, which could fall under the category of mathematical software (cs.MS). The stability analysis and efficiency considerations could also suggest a sub-category of scientific computing (cs.SC) or systems and control (cs.SI).
